        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 2:03PM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 203 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Sheffield, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Florence, Muscle Shoals, Sheffield, Tuscumbia, Rogersville, Killen,
Littleville, Lexington, Leighton, and St. Florian.
</description>
        <instruction>Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
